# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Whitelist .gitignore — publish ONLY the web app + docs.
# Everything else stays local: the Python research pipeline (pipeline/), research
# material and legacy snapshots (archive/, data/, materials/, *.xlsx), build/IDE
# cruft, and ALL credentials. This guarantees secrets and proprietary research can
# never be committed, even by accident.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ignore everything by default …
*

# … then explicitly allow the web app + docs.
!.gitignore
!.nojekyll
!README.md
!index.html

!styles/
!styles/**
!src/
!src/**
!api/
!api/**
!docs/
!docs/**

# Never publish credentials, even if a rule above would match them.
.env
.env.*
**/api.txt
**/tt_session.json
**/.factor_api_cache/
**/__pycache__/

# Re-allow the env template (must be the last word on this file).
!.env.example
